Open Eclipse
Click on help--> Click on Install new software
Click on ADD
you get a pop-up
Name: testNG
Loation:http://dl.bintray.com/testng-team/testng-eclipse-release/7.0.0/
Click on Add

This should download ans install the TestNG
To verify whethere its installed, Right click on your project
you should see "tesNG" there.

How to add testNG library to the project
Right click on your project-->build path
add Libraries --> TestNG 
Click on Finish

alternative method to add testNG library to the porject
Create a package e.g. testNG
Create a new Class without main method
Create a new method in this class
write the annotation i.e. @Test
you get an option now to add testNG library to your project
Then import the import org.testng.annotations.Test

e.g. code
package testNG;

import org.testng.annotations.Test;

public class Test0 {
@Test
public void demo() {
	
}

}

